Databases / Internal Services

A Bastion Host is the secure gateway to access private hosts inside a virtual cloud. By separating resources into public and private subnets, organizations
can protect sensitive data while still allowing necessary access. Understanding this architecture is essential for cloud security and managing 
infrastructure effectively.

Access: Needs a secure path (like VPN or Bastion Host) to connect from outside.
